<paragraph id="8BD936A3FFB3FF91FF41F88DFBDE04E1" blockId="1.[151,1437,1675,1989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">
This species is native to 
<collectingCountry id="F3717633FFB3FF91FE4AF88DFDAD0411" box="[460,558,1821,1845]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Australia</collectingCountry>
but has been introduced to 
<collectingCountry id="F3717633FFB3FF91FCD3F88EFC6B0411" box="[853,1000,1821,1845]" name="New Zealand" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, the 
<collectingCountry id="F3717633FFB3FF91FB9FF88DFB280411" box="[1049,1195,1821,1845]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">United States</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3717633FFB3FF91FB33F88DFAA10411" box="[1205,1314,1821,1845]" name="Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, the 
<collectingCountry id="F3717633FFB3FF91FAD2F88DFF7C047D" name="United Kingdom" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">United Kingdom</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3717633FFB3FF91FE8CF8D2FED6047D" box="[266,341,1858,1881]" name="France" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">France</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F3717633FFB3FF91FE08F8D1FE4E047D" box="[398,461,1857,1881]" name="Spain" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Spain</collectingCountry>
, including the Balearic and Canary archipelagos (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B52FFB3FF91FC62F8D2FA87047D" author="Alvarez-Presas, M. &amp; Mateos, E. &amp; Tudo, A. &amp; Jones, H. &amp; Riutort, M." box="[996,1284,1857,1884]" pageId="1" pageNumber="448" pagination="430" refId="ref2399" refString="Alvarez-Presas, M., Mateos, E., Tudo, A., Jones, H. &amp; Riutort, M. (2014) Diversity of introduced terrestrial flatworms in the Iberian Peninsula: A cautionary tale. PeerJ, 2, e 430. https: // doi. org / 10.7717 / peerj. 430" type="journal article" year="2014">
Álvarez-Presas 
<emphasis id="B912EAB1FFB3FF91FB08F8D2FB46047D" box="[1166,1221,1857,1881]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B52FFB3FF91FA89F8D1FE8F0459" author="Breugelmans, K. &amp; Cardona, J. Q. &amp; Artois, T. &amp; Jordaens, K. &amp; Backeljau, T." pageId="1" pageNumber="448" pagination="91 - 105" refId="ref2459" refString="Breugelmans, K., Cardona, J. Q., Artois, T., Jordaens, K. &amp; Backeljau, T. (2012) First report of the exotic blue land planarian, Caenoplana coerulea (Platyhelminthes, Geoplanidae), on Menorca (Balearic Islands, Spain). ZooKeys, 199, 91 - 105. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 199.3215" type="journal article" year="2012">
Breugelmans 
<emphasis id="B912EAB1FFB3FF91FF11F8F6FF4E0459" box="[151,205,1893,1917]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B52FFB3FF91FE90F8F5FD9D0459" author="Luis-Negrete, L. H. &amp; Brusa, F. &amp; Winsor, L." box="[278,542,1893,1917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="448" pagination="287 - 291" refId="ref3052" refString="Luis-Negrete, L. H., Brusa, F. &amp; Winsor, L. (2011) The blue land planarian Caenoplana coerulea, an invader in Argentina. Revista Mexicana de Biodiversidad, 82, 287 - 291. https: // doi. org / 10.22201 / ib. 20078706 e. 2011.1.450" type="journal article" year="2011">
Luis-Negrete 
<emphasis id="B912EAB1FFB3FF91FE2CF8F6FE5C0459" box="[426,479,1893,1917]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B52FFB3FF91FDAEF8F5FD6E0459" author="Suarez, D. &amp; Martin, S. &amp; Naranjo, M." box="[552,749,1893,1917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="448" pagination="67 - 74" refId="ref3441" refString="Suarez, D., Martin, S. &amp; Naranjo, M. (2018) First report of the invasive alien species Caenoplana coerulea Moseley, 1877 (Platyhelminthes, Tricladida, Geoplanidae) in the subterranean environment of the Canary Islands. Subterranean Biology, 26, 67 - 74. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / SUBTBIOL. 26.25921" type="journal article" year="2018">
Suárez 
<emphasis id="B912EAB1FFB3FF91FDF1F8F6FD2E0459" box="[631,685,1893,1917]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Here we provide the first record from Madeira. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B52FFB3FF91FB7DF8F6FE9A0485" author="Alvarez-Presas, M. &amp; Mateos, E. &amp; Tudo, A. &amp; Jones, H. &amp; Riutort, M." pageId="1" pageNumber="448" pagination="430" refId="ref2399" refString="Alvarez-Presas, M., Mateos, E., Tudo, A., Jones, H. &amp; Riutort, M. (2014) Diversity of introduced terrestrial flatworms in the Iberian Peninsula: A cautionary tale. PeerJ, 2, e 430. https: // doi. org / 10.7717 / peerj. 430" type="journal article" year="2014">
Álvarez-Presas 
<emphasis id="B912EAB1FFB3FF91FF11F81AFF4E0485" box="[151,205,1929,1953]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
found that 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D20FFB3FF91FE15F81AFD8C0485" authorityName="Moseley" authorityYear="1877" box="[403,527,1929,1953]" family="Geoplanidae" genus="Caenoplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="1" pageNumber="448" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="coerulea">
<emphasis id="B912EAB1FFB3FF91FE15F81AFD8C0485" box="[403,527,1929,1953]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">C. coerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was subdivided in three main clades. Our specimen from Madeira matches to a clade including sequences from 
<collectingCountry id="F3717633FFB3FF91FE28F83DFD9004E1" box="[430,531,1965,1989]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Australia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49A2F841FFB3FF91FD9BF83DFD0004E1" box="[541,643,1965,1989]" country="Spain" name="Catalunya" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Catalonia</collectingRegion>
and the 
<collectingRegion id="49A2F841FFB3FF91FD59F83DFCFD04E1" box="[735,894,1965,1989]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="F3717633FFB3FF91FC0AF83DFC4F04E1" box="[908,972,1965,1989]" name="Spain" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Spain</collectingCountry>
) (
<figureCitation id="135D2A26FFB3FF91FC67F83DFBD304E1" box="[993,1104,1965,1989]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,849,873]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,236,826]" captionTargetId="figure-34@1.[151,1436,236,826]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Maximum-likelihood tree of invasive terrestrial flatworms, based on COI sequences. Bootstrap values are presented only for main clades. Countries are indicated after GenBank accession number. Red: specimens sequenced in this study. A. Caenoplana coerulea tree. B. Endeavouria septemlineata tree. C. Obama nungara tree." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501323" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501323/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="448">Figure 1B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
